# Test your FastAPI endpoints

### Health check
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/
Accept: application/json

###

### ── Auth ────────────────────────────────────────────

### Register a new user
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123",
  "name": "Test User"
}

###

### Verify registration OTP (required before first login)
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/verify-registration-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "otp": "123456"
}

###

### Login
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### ── Test Database Connection (MySQL) ────────────────

POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/test-connection
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

{
  "database_type": "mysql",
  "host": "localhost",
  "port": 3306,
  "database_name": "my_app_db",
  "username": "root",
  "password": "secret"
}

###

### ── Test Database Connection (PostgreSQL) ───────────

POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/test-connection
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

{
  "database_type": "postgresql",
  "host": "localhost",
  "port": 5432,
  "database_name": "my_app_db",
  "username": "postgres",
  "password": "secret"
}

###

### ── Test Database Connection (MongoDB) ──────────────

POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/test-connection
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

{
  "database_type": "mongodb",
  "host": "localhost",
  "port": 27017,
  "database_name": "my_app_db",
  "username": "admin",
  "password": "secret"
}

###

### ── List saved databases ────────────────────────────

GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/databases
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### ── Get one saved database ──────────────────────────

GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/databases/<document_id>
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### ── Delete a saved database ─────────────────────────

DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/databases/<document_id>
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### ── BACKUPS ──────────────────────────────────────────

### Trigger a backup for a saved database config
### Replace <document_id> with the ID returned from /test-connection
POST http://127.0.0.1:8000/databases/<document_id>/backup
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### List all backups for a specific database config
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/databases/<document_id>/backups
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### List ALL backups for the current user (across all databases)
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/backups
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### Get metadata for a single backup
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/backups/<backup_id>
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### Download a backup file
GET http://127.0.0.1:8000/backups/<backup_id>/download
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### Delete a backup record (keep file on disk)
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/backups/<backup_id>
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

### Delete a backup record AND remove the file from disk
DELETE http://127.0.0.1:8000/backups/<backup_id>?delete_file=true
Authorization: Bearer <your_jwt_token>

###

